SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 167
By Crowe
A RESOLUTION to honor Jeff Kelly, Public Defender for the First
Judicial District, on the occasion of his
retirement.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should specially
recognize those estimable public servants who have dedicated themselves to improving the
quality of life for their fellow citizens; and
WHEREAS, Jeff Kelly, as Public Defender for the First Judicial District, has excelled in
his statutory mission of representing individuals who cannot afford a private attorney; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Kelly and his staff have accomplished this mission by ably representing
their clients in the courts of Carter, Johnson, Unicoi, and Washington counties; and
WHEREAS, Jeff Kelly is taking a much-deserved retirement after an exemplary career
with the Public Defenders Conference that spans thirty-five years; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Kelly was appointed First Judicial District Public Defender in September
2009 by Governor Phil Bredesen and was first elected to the post in 2010; and
WHEREAS, prior to his appointment, he served with distinction as an Assistant Public
Defender for the First Judicial District for twenty years; and
WHEREAS, recognized as a leader by his peers and colleagues, Jeff Kelly has served
the Tennessee Public Defenders Conference as a member of its Legislative, Technology, Ad-
Hoc Staffing Criteria, Ad-Hoc Administrative Staff Salary, Education, and Training committees;
and
WHEREAS, an alumnus of Milligan College, he earned his law degree at the University
of Tennessee; and
